Miss Alice, a priestess of Ilmater, is the caretaker of the Fort Cystana Orphanage. Her dimples and warm demeanor have endeared her to the children under her care.

Generations ago, the dwarven clan Dweomerpalm faced a plight: an expedition of mages from Thay were determined to gain control of the gem mines the dwarves controlled, and were bombarding the dwarven settlement with their destructive evocations. Having almost lost hope, the smiths of Keep Dweomer came up with an idea: They gathered every artisan and enchanter in the town to create suits of armor that would defy the elements themelves. Finally, enough such armors were finished to equip a retaliation army of the dwarves. Unfortunately for the Stout Folk, Thayvian diviners had revealed their plan and prepared something quite different. As the victoriously grinning dwarves charged, unshaken by the fireballs and bolts of lightning around them, devastating magic suddenly pierced and bent the poor dwarves minds. Those who didnt fall into a coma fled into every possible direction, chased by both imaginary fiends and the summoned servants of the wizards. Without much opposition, the Thayvians slaughtered the remaining inhabitants of Keep Dweomer and took over the mines they yearned for.

With the unlucky dwarves who got lost and usually killed somewhere in the Upperdark or the Cold Lands, the infamous Thaybreakers, later named Armors of Universal Resistance by dry scholarly types, spread across Faern and can still be found in monsters hoards or the private collections of lucky aventurers. They come in various shapes, but all are adorned with various gems which contain the protective enchantments. Tymora must be fond of you, for you are holding one such armor of legends.

Love magic for itself. Do not treat it just as a weapon to reshape the world to your will. True wisdom is knowing when not to use magic. Strive to use magic less as your powers develop, for often the threat or promise of its use outsripes its actual performance.

Magic is Art, the Gift of the Lady, and those who wield it are privileged in the extreme. Conduct yourself humbly, not proudly, while being mindful of this. Use the Art deftly and efficiently, not carelessly and recklessly. Seek always to learn and create new magic.

-Admittance to the Duchy of Fort Cystana-

   1. To enter duchy grounds, you are not permitted to bear a helmet or hood. Nor will you use any other method to cover your identity. Head coverings may be worn after verified entry.
   2. All weapons must remain sheathed unless permission is granted by local authorities, such as for self-defense against a criminal entity.
   3. 1. Duchy personnel may stop you to verify your identity and your business within the city, including to require you to remove your head covering for this purpose.
   3. 2. Failure to comply with such requests from personnel will result in violation of Penal Law  4.



-Ecclesiastical Law-

   1. Anyone who defiles the sanctity of the duchy shall be punished according to their deed.
   2. All sacred sites such as temples and shrines, as well as the clergy and personnel of Fort Cystana, are to be treated with due respect.
   3. Blasphemous statements against the gods and churches of Fort Cystana are forbidden.



-Banishment-

   1. Individuals whom fall into the following categories:
     - Half-blooded devil, demon, or daemon blooded kin
     - Undead
     - Palemasters
     - Fiends
     - Chromatic dragon kin
     - Followers of evil deities
     - Blackguards
     - Members of any Lolthite drow house
     - Any associate of Tarkuul
     - Shadovar
   2. Members, servants of the following states, organizations or institutions:
     - Red Wizards of Thay
     - Cult of the Dragon
     - Zhentarim
     - The Living City of Tarkuul
   3. Individuals listed on Fort Cystana's separate banishment list.
   4. Only the Council or Duke of Fort Cystana may approve permanent banishment of individuals.
   5. Temporary banishment of 24 hours may be given by guards and personnel of Fort Cystana if the individual has broken the law, or if criminal activity is reported.
   6. Individuals who have been banished have the right to request an appeal. Appeals will be observed by the Council of Fort Cystana.



-Penal Law-

   1. Murder and Manslaughter.
   2. Assault.
   3. Thievery and Banditry.
   4. Disturbing the Public Safety and Peace.
   5. Harassment.
   6. Bribery, Extortion, and Blackmail.
   7. Public Nudity and Vulgar Acts.
   8. Libel and Slander.



-Spellcasting Law-

   1. The casting of offensive spells is prohibited, except in defense of self or settlement or under controlled conditions for educational and training purposes.
   2. Casting of defensive spells is permitted as long as it neither causes disturbance of the peace nor breaches other laws.
   3. 1. The use of summons of good nature, no larger than a human being, are permitted within the city gates.
   3. 2. The use of other summons of non-evil nature which do not fit in the above category, of any size, are only permitted outside the city gates.
   3. 3. The summoner is responsible for all actions of a summoned creature, and will be given the punishment as if he had himself conducted the act.



-Due Process-

   1. Infractions against Penal Laws 1-3 will result in arrest, to be followed by a trial overseen by a judge appointed by the Council of Fort Cystana.
   2. 1. Infractions against Penal Laws 4-8 and any Spellcasting Law will result in a fine of 20,000 gold coins on the first offense.
   2. 2. Temporary banishment from the city may follow with subsequent offenses.
   2. 3. Guards may arrest continuously repeat offenders at their discretion, so that a trial may be conducted.
